1. 降阶Landen变换：
   $$k(2\tau)=\frac{1-k'(\tau)}{1+k'(\tau)}.$$
2. 当$\tau=i$时，$k(i)=\tfrac1{\sqrt2}$，因此
   $$k'(i)=\sqrt{1-\frac1{2}}=\frac1{\sqrt2}.$$
3. 因此
   $$k(2i)=\frac{1-\tfrac1{\sqrt2}}{1+\tfrac1{\sqrt2}}
            =\frac{\sqrt2-1}{\sqrt2+1}
            =(\sqrt2-1)^2=3-2\sqrt2.$$
4. 接着
   $$k'(2i)=\sqrt{1-(3-2\sqrt2)^2}
            =\sqrt{1-(17-12\sqrt2)}
            =\sqrt{12\sqrt2-16}
            =2\sqrt{3\sqrt2-4}.$$
5. 最后
   $$k(4i)
     =\frac{1-k'(2i)}{1+k'(2i)}
     =\frac{1-2\sqrt{3\sqrt2-4}}{1+2\sqrt{3\sqrt2-4}}.$$
